eu.etaxonomy.cdm.model.name
Class NomenclaturalStatusType

java.lang.Object
  eu.etaxonomy.cdm.model.common.CdmBase
      eu.etaxonomy.cdm.model.common.VersionableEntity
          eu.etaxonomy.cdm.model.common.TermBase

All Implemented Interfaces:
ICdmBase, ILoadableTerm, Serializable, Comparable<NomenclaturalStatusType>
public class NomenclaturalStatusType
extends OrderedTermBase<NomenclaturalStatusType>

The class representing categories of nomenclatural status (like "invalid", "conserved" or "novum") to qualify the use of a particular taxon name string depending on its nomenclatural reference (original publication), on its nomenclatural code and on possible decisions of the corresponding competent authorities. Unfortunately the ICBN and the ICZN use sometimes different words for the same meaning or the same word for different meanings (for instance "valid" and "legitimate").

A standard (ordered) list of nomenclatural status type instances will be automatically created as the project starts. But this class allows to extend this standard list by creating new instances of additional nomenclatural status types if needed. The present standard list follows the ICBN terminology.

This class corresponds more or less to:

  • NomenclaturalNoteTypeTerm according to the TDWG ontology
  • NomenclaturalNoteType according to the TCS

Version:
1.0

a.mueller

isInvalidType

public boolean isInvalidType()
Returns the boolean value indicating whether this nomenclatural status type is itself "invalid" or a kind of "invalid" (true) or not (false) - this corresponds to "not available" for zoological names -. Returns false if this nomenclatural status type is null. The use of "invalid" taxon names should be avoided.
A taxon name is "invalid" if it is not "valid"; this means that the taxon name:
  • has not been effectively published or
  • has a form which does not comply with the rules of the nomenclature code or
  • is not accompanied by a description or diagnosis or by a reference to such a previously published description or diagnosis

See Also:
VALID(), isIllegitimateType(), DefinedTermBase.getKindOf()

isLegitimateType

public boolean isLegitimateType()
Returns the boolean value indicating whether this nomenclatural status type is itself "legitimate" or a kind of "legitimate" (true) or not (false). - this corresponds to "valid" for zoological names -. Returns false if this nomenclatural status type is null.
A "valid" ("available") taxon name, unless "rejected", is "legitimate" if it was not "superfluous" when published or has been later "conserved".

See Also:
isInvalidType(), isIllegitimateType(), DefinedTermBase.getKindOf()

isIllegitimateType

public boolean isIllegitimateType()
Returns the boolean value indicating whether this nomenclatural status type is itself "illegitimate" or a kind of "illegitimate" (true) or not (false) - this corresponds to "invalid" for zoological names -. Returns false if this nomenclatural status type is null.
A "valid" ("available") taxon name, unless "conserved" or "sanctioned", is "illegitimate" if it was "superfluous" when published or has been later "rejected".

See Also:
VALID(), isInvalidType(), ILLEGITIMATE(), CONSERVED(), SANCTIONED(), DefinedTermBase.getKindOf()

AMBIGUOUS

public static final NomenclaturalStatusType AMBIGUOUS()
Returns the nomenclatural status type "ambiguous". A "valid" ("available") taxon name is "ambiguous" if it has been used so long by different authors in different senses (other than the originally intended) that it has become a persistent cause of error and confusion.
An "ambiguous" taxon name is treated as if "rejected" and is therefore also "illegitimate" ("invalid" for zoological names).

See Also:
VALID(), REJECTED(), isIllegitimateType()

DOUBTFUL

public static final NomenclaturalStatusType DOUBTFUL()
Returns the nomenclatural status type "doubtful" (dubious). A "valid" ("available") taxon name is "doubtful" if its application is uncertain; the confusion being derived from an incomplete or confusing description.
A "doubtful" taxon name is treated as if "rejected" and is therefore also "illegitimate" (("invalid" for zoological names).

See Also:
VALID(), REJECTED(), isIllegitimateType()

CONFUSUM

public static final NomenclaturalStatusType CONFUSUM()
Returns the nomenclatural status type "confusum". A "valid" ("available") taxon name is "confusum" if it has been widely and persistently used for a taxon or taxa not including its type.
A "confusum" taxon name is treated as if "rejected" and is therefore also "illegitimate" ("invalid" for zoological names).

See Also:
VALID(), REJECTED(), isIllegitimateType()

ILLEGITIMATE

public static final NomenclaturalStatusType ILLEGITIMATE()
Returns the nomenclatural status type "illegitimate" ("invalid" for zoological names). A "valid" ("available") taxon name, unless "conserved" or "sanctioned", is "illegitimate" if it was "superfluous" when published or has been later "rejected".

See Also:
VALID(), SUPERFLUOUS(), REJECTED()

SUPERFLUOUS

public static final NomenclaturalStatusType SUPERFLUOUS()
Returns the nomenclatural status type "superfluous". A "valid" ("available") taxon name is "superfluous" if, when published, the taxon to which it was applied, as circumscribed by its author, definitely included the type of a name which ought to have been adopted, or of which the epithet ought to have been adopted, under the rules of the nomenclature code, and if it has not been later declared "conserved" or "sanctioned" by the competent authorities.
A "superfluous" taxon name is therefore also "illegitimate" ("invalid" for zoological names).

See Also:
VALID(), CONSERVED(), SANCTIONED(), isIllegitimateType()

REJECTED

public static final NomenclaturalStatusType REJECTED()
Returns the nomenclatural status type "rejected". A "valid" ("available") taxon name is "rejected" if, even though by the strict application of the rules of the nomenclature code, and especially of the principle of priority, it should be "legitimate" ("valid" for zoological names), competent authorities decided to handle it as "illegitimate".
A "rejected" taxon name is therefore also "illegitimate" ("invalid" for zoological names). A "rejected" taxon name is always rejected in favour of a "conserved" taxon name.

See Also:
VALID(), isLegitimateType(), isIllegitimateType(), CONSERVED(), NameRelationshipType.CONSERVED_AGAINST()

UTIQUE_REJECTED

public static final NomenclaturalStatusType UTIQUE_REJECTED()
Returns the nomenclatural status type "utique rejected". A "valid" ("available") taxon name is "utique rejected" if it is rejected outright (without being rejected in favour of a "conserved" taxon name).
An "utique rejected" taxon name is therefore also "illegitimate" ("invalid" for zoological names).

See Also:
REJECTED(), VALID(), isIllegitimateType(), CONSERVED()

CONSERVED_PROP

public static final NomenclaturalStatusType CONSERVED_PROP()
Returns the nomenclatural status type "proposed to be conserved". A "valid" ("available") taxon name is "proposed to be conserved" if, even though by the strict application of the rules of the nomenclature code, and especially of the principle of priority, it is "illegitimate" ("invalid" for zoological names), it has been submitted to competent authorities in order to decide whether it should be handled as "legitimate".
A "proposed to be conserved" taxon name is therefore still "illegitimate" ("invalid" for zoological names).

See Also:
VALID(), isIllegitimateType(), isLegitimateType(), CONSERVED(), NameRelationshipType.CONSERVED_AGAINST()

ORTHOGRAPHY_CONSERVED_PROP

public static final NomenclaturalStatusType ORTHOGRAPHY_CONSERVED_PROP()
Returns the nomenclatural status type "proposed to be conserved (orthography)". A taxon name is "proposed to be conserved (orthography)" if, even though originally published with another spelling, it has been submitted to competent authorities in order to decide whether the proposed alternative spelling should be "conserved".
A "proposed to be conserved (orthography)" taxon name is therefore still "illegitimate" ("invalid" for zoological names).

See Also:
isIllegitimateType(), CONSERVED_PROP(), CONSERVED(), NameRelationshipType.ORTHOGRAPHIC_VARIANT(), NameRelationshipType.CONSERVED_AGAINST()

LEGITIMATE

public static final NomenclaturalStatusType LEGITIMATE()
Returns the nomenclatural status type "legitimate" ("valid" for zoological names). A "valid" ("available") taxon name, unless "rejected", is "legitimate" if it was not "superfluous" when published or has been later "conserved".

See Also:
VALID(), SUPERFLUOUS(), CONSERVED()

ALTERNATIVE

public static final NomenclaturalStatusType ALTERNATIVE()
Returns the nomenclatural status type "alternative". A family botanical name is "alternative" if it is a classical name long in use, in some cases even before 1753, and is considered as "valid" although it does not follow the rules for family names (see Article 18 of the ICBN).
An "alternative" taxon name is treated as if "conserved" and is therefore also "legitimate".

See Also:
VALID(), CONSERVED(), isLegitimateType(), NameRelationshipType.ALTERNATIVE_NAME()

NOVUM

public static final NomenclaturalStatusType NOVUM()
Returns the nomenclatural status type "novum". A "valid" ("available") taxon name is "novum" if it has been created in order either to replace an earlier name that is "illegitimate" or to avoid the building of a "later homonym".
A "novum" taxon name is therefore also "legitimate" ("valid" for zoological names).

See Also:
VALID(), isIllegitimateType(), NameRelationshipType.REPLACED_SYNONYM(), NameRelationshipType.BLOCKING_NAME_FOR()

UTIQUE_REJECTED_PROP

public static final NomenclaturalStatusType UTIQUE_REJECTED_PROP()
Returns the nomenclatural status type "proposed to be utique rejected". A "valid" ("available") taxon name is "proposed to be utique rejected" if, even though by the strict application of the rules of the nomenclature code, and especially of the principle of priority, it is "legitimate" ("valid" for zoological names), it has been submitted to competent authorities in order to decide whether it should be handled as "illegitimate" (without to be rejected in favour of a "conserved" taxon name).
A "proposed to be utique rejected" taxon name is therefore still "legitimate" ("valid" for zoological names).

See Also:
VALID(), isLegitimateType(), isIllegitimateType(), REJECTED(), REJECTED_PROP()

ORTHOGRAPHY_CONSERVED

public static final NomenclaturalStatusType ORTHOGRAPHY_CONSERVED()
Returns the nomenclatural status type "conserved (orthography)". A taxon name is "conserved (orthography)" if competent authorities decided to conserve a different spelling to the one published originally.
A "conserved (orthography)" taxon name is "conserved" and hence "legitimate" ("valid" for zoological names).

See Also:
isLegitimateType(), CONSERVED(), ORTHOGRAPHY_CONSERVED_PROP(), NameRelationshipType.ORTHOGRAPHIC_VARIANT(), NameRelationshipType.CONSERVED_AGAINST()

REJECTED_PROP

public static final NomenclaturalStatusType REJECTED_PROP()
Returns the nomenclatural status type "proposed to be rejected". A "valid" ("available") taxon name is "proposed to be rejected" if, even though by the strict application of the rules of the nomenclature code, and especially of the principle of priority, it should be "legitimate" ("valid" for zoological names), it has been submitted to competent authorities in order to decide whether it should be handled as "illegitimate".
A "proposed to be rejected" taxon name is therefore still "legitimate" ("valid" for zoological names). A "proposed to be rejected" taxon name is always to be rejected in favour of a "proposed to be conserved" taxon name.

See Also:
VALID(), isLegitimateType(), isIllegitimateType(), REJECTED(), CONSERVED_PROP(), NameRelationshipType.CONSERVED_AGAINST()

CONSERVED

public static final NomenclaturalStatusType CONSERVED()
Returns the nomenclatural status type "conserved". A "valid" ("available") taxon name is "conserved" if, even though by the strict application of the rules of the nomenclature code, and especially of the principle of priority, it should be "illegitimate" ("invalid" for zoological names), competent authorities decided to handle it as "legitimate".
A "conserved" taxon name is therefore also "legitimate" ("valid" for zoological names).

See Also:
VALID(), isIllegitimateType(), isLegitimateType(), NameRelationshipType.CONSERVED_AGAINST()

SANCTIONED

public static final NomenclaturalStatusType SANCTIONED()
Returns the nomenclatural status type "sanctioned". Botanical names for fungi are "sanctioned" if they were published in the opera mentioned in Article 13.1d of the ICBN.
A "sanctioned" taxon name is treated as if "conserved" and is therefore also "legitimate".

See Also:
VALID(), CONSERVED(), isLegitimateType()

INVALID

public static final NomenclaturalStatusType INVALID()
Returns the nomenclatural status type "invalid" (this corresponds to "not available" for zoological names). The use of "invalid" taxon names should be avoided.
A taxon name is "invalid" if it is not "valid"; this means that the taxon name:
  • has not been effectively published or
  • has a form which does not comply with the rules of the nomenclature code or
  • is not accompanied by a description or diagnosis or by a reference to such a previously published description or diagnosis

See Also:
VALID(), isInvalidType(), ILLEGITIMATE()

NUDUM

public static final NomenclaturalStatusType NUDUM()
Returns the nomenclatural status type "nudum". A taxon name is "nudum" if its publication is not accompanied by a description or diagnosis or by a reference to such a previously published description or diagnosis.
A "nudum" taxon name is therefore also "invalid" ("not available" for zoological names).

See Also:
isInvalidType()

COMBINATION_INVALID

public static final NomenclaturalStatusType COMBINATION_INVALID()
Returns the nomenclatural status type "invalid combination". A bi- or trinomial is an "invalid combination" if its author did not definitely associate the final epithet with the name of the genus or species, or with its abbreviation.
An "invalid combination" taxon name is therefore also "invalid" ("not available" for zoological names).

See Also:
isInvalidType()

PROVISIONAL

public static final NomenclaturalStatusType PROVISIONAL()
Returns the nomenclatural status type "provisional". A taxon name is "provisional" if it has not been yet effectively published.
A "provisional" taxon name is therefore also "invalid" ("not available" for zoological names).

See Also:
isInvalidType()

VALID

public static final NomenclaturalStatusType VALID()
Returns the nomenclatural status type "valid" (this corresponds to "available" for zoological names).
A taxon name is "valid" if it:
  • has been effectively published and
  • has a form which complies with the rules of the nomenclature code and
  • is accompanied by a description or diagnosis or by a reference to such a previously published description or diagnosis

See Also:
INVALID(), LEGITIMATE()

SUBNUDUM

public static final NomenclaturalStatusType SUBNUDUM()
Returns the nomenclatural status type "subnudum". This type is not covered by nomenclature codes. It appears sometimes in literature and represents the opinion of the author who considers the taxon name to be unusable for an unambiguous taxonomic use.

See Also:
AMBIGUOUS(), CONFUSUM()

OPUS_UTIQUE_OPPR

public static final NomenclaturalStatusType OPUS_UTIQUE_OPPR()
Returns the nomenclatural status type "opus utique oppressum". This type relates to article 32.7 (old ICBN) and article 32.9 as well as App. 6 (new ICBN). This is a reference list of botanical opera, in which all taxon names (or names of a certain rank) are oppressed. Such a name has the status "invalid" but in contrary to "rejected" not a single name is rejected by the commission but an opus with regard to the validity of all taxon names occurring in it.
An "opus utique oppressum" taxon name is therefore also "invalid" ("not available" for zoological names).

See Also:
isInvalidType()
